So I was stopped by someone the other day and complimented on my
courteous driving and allowing people to pass, I wasn't, the gas pedal
was floored.

A state patrol driver commented on my driving the speed limit and
staying to the right for faster drivers, My gas pedal was floored.

The city police smiled while bicycles passed me, thinking I was being a
nice Joe. I wasn't, the gas pedal was floored.

It's kind of like a light switch, up for off and down for on, relatively
speaking.

